== Python Server ==

Tiny server for python script execution.

== Overview ==

After building program using Make utility, further executables are generated:
1. PyServer - connection manager.
2. PyExec   - python script execution server.
3. PySender - program for sending python files to PythonServer for execution.

== Usage example ==

1. Start python server in shell:
	cd ~/PythonServer
	./PyServer

   or start python server as a daemon:
	./PyServer --d

   and stop PythonServer daemon:
	./PyServer --stop

   start python server as a daemon with root privileges, while PyExec will be running with user (uid=1000) privileges:
	sudo ./PyServer --d --u 1000

2. Send python script "example.py":
	cd ~/PythonServer
	./PySender localhost 5555 example.py


Shell command for getting additional information about command line parameters:
	./PyServer --help
